infinite demand for justice named by Derrida, to 
remember its limits -the limits of its concepts, 
values, norms, and regulations -in "responsibility 
towards memory." 105 

It is at this point that a coming, future justice of 
the law makes its departure. Legal justice first re-
quires insofar a sense of historical responsibility 
that recognizes history not as given, but as aban-
doned. 106 It also means responsibility for the fu-
