their own narratives, thereby seeking to empathize 
with other people's worlds of experience, in order 
ultimately perhaps to find a provisional justice in 
the here and now. The search is directed towards 
making possible new things, towards social devel-
opment opportunities and individual leeway, for 
example, or, to put it another way: towards open fu-
tures, supported by the legal awareness that things 
