Wiethölter describes the now necessary search 
"for the unknown in the reality of law" 129 : 

"It has its eyes on not another law, nor an other 
than law, but the other (a possible other) of law, 
its redeemable surpluses of possibility rather 
than its unredeemed surpluses of promise. All 
that is possible is possible." 130 

